<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-28T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-28T14:00:00-05:00" n="415" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.654/63: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Italy (<persName type="to">Garrett</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-28T14:00:00-05:00">February 28, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>10. Your No. 7, February 23, 11 a.m. Full powers will be forwarded by
                                the next pouch.</p>
                            <p>You are authorized to sign if our draft is accepted. Should the
                                Italian Government propose any modifications, you are instructed to
                                submit them to the Department for approval.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>